Date: 0/4/1999
Source: Official New Zealand Road Code, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 78
Edition:
Quote: Sunstrike can occur at sunrise or sunset, when the sun's rays hit your windscreen at a low angle. This can make it difficult, or even impossible to see... Be prepared for possible sunstrike when driving at sunrise or sunset, particularly when turning or driving towards the sun.
